  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in Senate", 
    "date": "2019-05-23T04:00:00Z", 
    "text": "Shareholder Protection Act of 2019\n\nThis bill requires shareholder authorization of certain political expenditures by an issuer. A violation of this requirement shall be considered\u00a0a breach of fiduciary duty, and the officers and directors who authorized the expenditure shall be subject to joint and several liability. An issuer must require a board vote with respect to political expenditures in excess of $50,000 and, within 48 hours, make publicly available the individual votes of each board member."
  }, 
